The paper focuses on concentration inequalities and their applications in information theory, communications, and coding. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of concentration inequalities in learning theory and dynamical systems, which fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively. The paper also discusses the use of concentration inequalities in theoretical computer science, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions lossless source coding with side information, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
